<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1230,2013]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1374,1400]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[431,543,1375,1401]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaciba" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[431,543,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. yaciba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,662,1375,1401]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[548,662,1375,1401]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[870,1018,1375,1400]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis">
<emphasis box="[870,1018,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1032,1187,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–224" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,1054,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-312@56.[160,1427,1043,1895]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 221–224. Meri pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov., male (IBSP 20795), left palp (221 prolateral, 222 ventral, 223 retrolateral, 224 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; mr—membranous region; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA— retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; tp—tegular protrusion; vb—ventral branch of RTA. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550350/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 221–224</figureCitation>
) by the palp with RTA with a ventral branch (
<figureCitation box="[402,499,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 298</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from the latter species by RTA distally pointed with ventral branch roughly three times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[678,833,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–291" captionStartId="70.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,317,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-93@70.[155,1432,309,1769]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURES 285–291. Meri vanini spec. nov. 285–288 male (MPEG 30859, paratype), left palp (285 prolateral, 286 ventral, 287 retrolateral, 288 detail of embolus, ventral); 289–291 female (MZSP 37241, paratype) (289 epigyne, 290 vulva, 291 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550516/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 288–289</figureCitation>
) and embolus with subdistal projection hook-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[160,256,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 300</figureCitation>
) (RTA distally blunt with ventral branch triangular, slightly longer than wide and embolus with subdistal projection long, mediad and laminar in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[600,750,1519,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis">
<emphasis box="[600,750,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1083,1233,1519,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1083,1233,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1241,1371,1519,1545]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1241,1371,1519,1545]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 225–230" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1364,1388]" captionTargetBox="[228,1355,464,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-168@57.[221,1366,453,1341]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 225–230. Meri pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov. 225–227 female (MNHN 1140, syntype) (225 epigyne, 226 vulva, 227 schematic course of internal duct system); 228–230 female (MNHN 1140, syntype) (228 epigyne, 229 vulva, 230 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550352/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 225–227</figureCitation>
) by the epigyne with MS widest anteriorly, partly covering LL and EP triangular. They are distinguished by the MS with posterior margin anterior to that of LL and EP more than 1.5 times longer than wide (MS with posterior margins in line with posterior margin of LL and EP slightly longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1046,1196,1627,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1046,1196,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1203,1331,1627,1653]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1203,1331,1627,1653]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
